  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Chop your <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> in half, lengthways</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with your <strong>ground paprika</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 15 min or until starting to brown</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1690285524042-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1690285524042-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1690285524042-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1690285524042-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1690285524042-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, tear your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>red onion[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>into wedges</p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>into wedges</p><p>Cut your <strong>cucumber</strong> in half lengthways, then slice finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1690285528649-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1690285528649-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1690285528649-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1690285528649-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1690285528649-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes have been in the oven for 15 min, remove the tray[s] and add the <strong>torn ciabatta</strong>, <strong>onion wedges</strong>, <strong>tomato wedges</strong>, <strong>half </strong>your <strong>dried oregano </strong>and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) to the other side</p><p>Add a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for a final 15 min or until the potatoes and the ciabatta is golden and crispy</p>",
      "order": 3,
